'''Impetigo''' is a very [[wikt:contagious|contagious]] [[bacteria]]l [[skin]] infection. It is most common in pre-school [[child]]ren.<ref>[http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Impetigo/Pages/Introduction.aspx NHS Impetigo]</ref> People who play close-contact [[sports]] like [[Rugby football|rugby]] and [[American football]] are also at risk. Impetigo is not very common in [[adult]]s. Impetigo can also be called ''school sores''.<ref>[http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/bhcv2/bhcarticles.nsf/pages/Impetigo_or_school_sores?OpenDocument Impetigo — school sores — Better Health Channel]</ref>

